OL,3,CPoliticians vote to allow assisted
OL,4,Cdying in Jersey
OL,6,Fpoliticians have voted to allow people
OL,7,Fwith terminal illnesses to end their
OL,8,Flives.
OL,10,FAfter a long and emotional debate,
OL,11,FDeputies supported introducing an
OL,12,Fassisted dying law for those with less
OL,13,Fthan six months to live, or 12 months
OL,14,Fif they have a neurodegenerative
OL,15,Fcondition, by 32 votes to 14 with no
OL,16,Fabsentations.
OL,18,FA person must also be 18 or over and
OL,19,Fliving in Jersey for at least a year
OL,20,Fto be eligible.
