OL,3,CPoliticians vote to allow assisted
OL,4,Cdying in Jersey
OL,6,FThe landmark decision is one of the
OL,7,Fmost significant in the island's
OL,8,Fhistory and puts it on the path to
OL,9,Fbecoming the first place in the
OL,10,FBritish Isles to legalise assisted
OL,11,Fdying.
OL,13,FHowever, while 'Route 1' was approved,
OL,14,F'Route 2' was rejected by 27 votes to
OL,15,F19 with no absentations.
OL,17,FIt means those with incurable physical
OL,18,Fconditions experiencing "unbearable
OL,19,Fsuffering" will not be allowed to end
OL,20,Ftheir lives unless they already
OL,21,Fqualify under 'Route 1'.
